    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Peel and chop the <strong>sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-prawns-and-mashed-sweet-potato/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>&nbsp;and bring to the boil over a high heat</p> <p>Cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p> <p>Once done, drain the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong>,&nbsp;return them to the pot and cover them to keep warm</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-prawns-and-mashed-sweet-potato/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong><br /><br />Cut the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-prawns-and-mashed-sweet-potato/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>&nbsp;over a medium-high heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the<strong>&nbsp;sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong> and<strong> dried&nbsp;oregano</strong> and cook for 1 min&nbsp;</p> <p>Tip: watch the garlic like a hawk to make sure it doesn't burn!</p> <p>Add the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to break down</p> <p>Re-boil a full kettle</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-prawns-and-mashed-sweet-potato/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes have broken down, add the <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>tomato paste</strong> with 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and cook for 1-2 min, stirring until everything's combined</p> <p>Add the <strong>prawns</strong> and cook for a further 3-4 min or until cooked through &ndash; these are your <strong>garlic chilli prawns</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-prawns-and-mashed-sweet-potato/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>shredded spring greens</strong> to a colander over the sink and pour over all of the <strong>boiled water</strong>&nbsp;until bright green and wilted</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-prawns-and-mashed-sweet-potato/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> and mash them until smooth</p> <p>Tip: if the mash has cooled down, warm it through over a low heat, stirring constantly</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-prawns-and-mashed-sweet-potato/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> garlic chilli prawns</strong> over the <strong>sweet potato mash</strong> with the <strong>spring greens</strong> to the side</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
